The development of abiological catalysts that can function in biological systems 
is an emerging subject of importance with significant ramifications in synthetic 
chemistry and the life sciences. Herein we report a biocompatible ruthenium 
complex [Cp(MQA)Ru(C3H5)](+)PF6(-) 2 (Cp = cyclopentadienyl, MQA = 
